COVID19 Update(Nigeria): 
confirmed 0, deaths 0, recovered 0 Nigeria on Tuesday confirmed 148 new cases of the Coronavirus infection, taking the country’s total to 2950. According to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, Lagos, the epicentre of the pandemic in the country, led in the number of new cases with 43, followed closely by Kano State with 32. The numbers of new cases in other states were as follows:14-Zamfara, 10-FCT, 9-Katsina, 7-Taraba, 6-Borno, 6-Ogun, 5-Oyo, 3-Edo, 3-Kaduna, 3-Bauchi, 2-Adamawa, 2-Gombe,  and one in each of Plateau, Sokoto, and Kebbi. NCDC said a total of 481 patients have been treated and discharged, while 98 have died. Source: Business Day Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription. COVID19 Update(Nigeria): run-away COVID-19 patient The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Tuesday recorded 148 new cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19), bringing the total number of infections in Nigeria to 2,950. NCDC announced this on its website on Tuesday night. “On the 5th of May 2020, 148 new confirmed cases… May 5, 2020 In "News" COVID19 Update(Nigeria): Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Tuesday confirmed a total number of 148 new coronavirus cases and five deaths in the last 24 hours. Nigeria's populated city Lagos and Kano states have the highest numbers. While Lagos recorded 43 new cases, Kano recorded 32 new cases. Zamfara State… May 5, 2020 In "News" COVID19 Update(Nigeria): Five new cases of Coronavirus (Covid-19) have been reported in Nigeria late Sunday night making a total of 323 cases in the country. According to the figures released by Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Lagos and Kwara States have 2 new cases each while Katsina recorded 1… April 12, 2020 In "News"